Bandari coach, Andre Cassa Mbungo commended his players for their performance. 

“It is the first time Vihiga is losing the game by more than a goal and our win shows our striking force is working well,” said Mbungo. 

Vihiga United coach Sammy Okoth attributed the defeat to loss of concentration by his players. 

“We’ve been punished because my players showed fatigue and I’ve to work hard to get the team ready for our next fixture against Western Stima,” Said Okoth. High-flying Wazito have a date with 2008 champions Mathare United. Henry Meja hit the winner for the Brewers in the 81st minute. He says the President's support for the Sh4.5 billion car grant contributed to the outcome. Opposition says the result is an "electoral holdup" and urges the public to protest against it. Somalia, facing an electoral impasse, has seen cases of Covid-19 rise significantly this month.